Actress Iyabo Ojo has stated she is in a relationship with a man but would rather keep his identity away from the prying eyes of social media. The 44-year-old media personality, who is a cast in the newly released project “Real House Wives of Lagos” stated this in a video snippet of the television series. Ojo, while referring to herself as a ‘fine girl’, noted she isn’t going to flaunt her new lover on social media until they’re officially married. “I have someone in my life we have been together for a while but he is a very private person and he does not like the social media life; he does not like all that.   Tekno to Davido: don’t talk to me again if…     Find my man, DJ Cuppy tells Mr Eazi, sister     Teni gifts SUV for mother of three   “He just wants to be in his own corner because he feels that I am always attacked on social media. “He does not want the social media people, that is, my fans, the haters, to drag him into it. “I do not think I want to celebrate anyone until I am getting married again. So, I don’t talk about my love life but, yes, I do have someone in my life. Fine girl like me must get bobo,” she said.